about.summary: This R-package contains examples from the book "Regression for Categorical Data", Tutz 2012, Cambridge University Press. The names of the examples refer to the chapter and the data set that is used.
This R-package contains examples from the book "Regression for Categorical Data", Tutz 2012, Cambridge University Press. The names of the examples refer to the chapter and the data set that is used.

name: r-catdata
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.2.2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-catdata
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/catdata_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/catdata/catdata_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7297062e6b1bd3a3046b8762fee8832b5c66ec434b2bc913f4cd6c06a23f7d92

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('catdata')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('catdata')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=catdata
  license: GPL-2.0-only
  summary: This R-package contains examples from the book "Regression for Categorical Data",
    Tutz 2012, Cambridge University Press. The names of the examples refer to the chapter
    and the data set that is used.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
